<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-05-30T04:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-05-30T04:16:00-05:00" n="525" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">871.63/18: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-05-30T11:00:00+01:44"><hi rend="italic">May 30,
                                        1924—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:50
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>19. Mining bill is before Parliament now. I have received copies of new
                            draft from Minister of Foreign Affairs, but oil interests find <pb facs="0700" n="606" xml:id="pg_606"/> it just as unsatisfactory as
                            previous draft. The Legation likewise considers the bill still very
                            unsatisfactory, the changes appearing to be unimportant.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>